
After unpacking the sources zip, trying to build with "cmake ." and "make" might fail
with compilation errors about architecture not supporting __wfi() etc...

On my system this can be fixed simply by running "cmake ." again ... why? No idea.

You might want to copy pico_sdk_import.cmake from your pico-sdk directory
and don't remember to 'git submodule update --init' after cloning the SDK
or you'll get missing includes for lwip and cyw43.
